20:16.417 --> 20:18.117
- ( Glass shatters )
- ( Car alarm blaring )

20:18.185 --> 20:20.253
- I think we should probably run.
- Yeah, let's.

20:23.185 --> 20:24.753
All: Go Brawlers!

20:24.754 --> 20:26.153
Tucker: We're on a roll!

20:26.289 --> 20:28.690
All thanks
to my lovely co-captain.

20:28.759 --> 20:30.492
Riley even made up
with the umpire.

20:30.560 --> 20:33.262
Turns out he really
does need new glasses.

20:33.629 --> 20:36.632
- Ben.
- Hey, Mom. Come to help us celebrate?

20:36.699 --> 20:39.033
No, more like hide out.
Honey, you have to help me.

20:39.101 --> 20:41.736
- What's wrong?
- Mom, what about this guy?

20:42.554 --> 20:43.738
I don't know, honey.

20:44.106 --> 20:46.107
The fear in his eyes
is a bit of a turn off.

20:46.925 --> 20:49.092
Beat it.

20:49.160 --> 20:50.328
What about that guy
over there?

20:50.396 --> 20:51.929
Hey, you!
Don't worry.

20:51.997 --> 20:53.398
I'm gonna find a guy
that makes you happy.

20:53.465 --> 20:56.333
Okay.

20:56.401 --> 20:58.768
He seems to be
getting better.

20:58.836 --> 21:01.270
- Thanks for talking to him.
- How did you know--?

21:01.338 --> 21:04.106
Hey, I know my boy's work
when I see it.

21:04.174 --> 21:07.243
Like I always say,
thank God for my Ben.

21:07.310 --> 21:10.979
- ( Chanting ) Do the Wheeler, do the Wheeler...
- What is Riley doing?

21:11.048 --> 21:12.981
Ben: I believe it's
called the Wheeler.

21:14.751 --> 21:17.752
Well, honey, throw her a dollar.
Otherwise this is just sad.

